1
00:00:04,747 --> 00:00:08,077
Try to know that one thing
upon knowing which everything is known.

2
00:00:08,178 --> 00:00:13,638
[Love | You Get Everything]

3
00:00:14,171 --> 00:00:17,111
They say, “Oh, if you haven’t done this 
you haven’t lived!”

4
00:00:17,111 --> 00:00:19,911
And that makes me want 
to follow my heart.

5
00:00:19,921 --> 00:00:24,981
It means it’s a particular level 
of intensity of feeling,

6
00:00:25,141 --> 00:00:26,621
of appreciation.

7
00:00:26,621 --> 00:00:28,254
You’re a scientist, Brand.

8
00:00:28,254 --> 00:00:30,514
So listen to me.

9
00:00:30,604 --> 00:00:35,724
When I say that love
isn’t something we invented. It’s …

10
00:00:36,577 --> 00:00:39,477
… observable, powerful.

11
00:00:40,993 --> 00:00:42,533
It has to mean something.

12
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:49,883
Many things that we value
are not objectively verifiable—

13
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:52,973
like humour,

14
00:00:52,973 --> 00:00:56,813
like what we like things
that are funny. Why should we?

15
00:00:56,813 --> 00:01:00,263
I mean humans 
are the only animals who really laugh.

16
00:01:00,263 --> 00:01:02,003
They can go,
“No, there’s a laughing hyena!”

17
00:01:02,003 --> 00:01:05,453
—No, that doesn’t count.
[Laughing]

18
00:01:05,913 --> 00:01:07,163
Well, I’m just saying …

19
00:01:07,163 --> 00:01:10,213
So, humans, we laugh, 
we cry …

20
00:01:10,213 --> 00:01:12,613
You can say, “Oh, animals wail!” 
That’s true,

21
00:01:12,613 --> 00:01:13,833
because they’re approaching human—

22
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:16,543
they wail when their babies
are taken away and things like that.

23
00:01:16,543 --> 00:01:19,713
You start feeling.
So what we’re all about is feeling.

24
00:01:19,713 --> 00:01:24,343
Love has meaning, yes.
Social utility, social bonding, child rearing …

25
00:01:24,343 --> 00:01:28,023
We love people who have died.
Where’s the social utility in that?

26
00:01:29,238 --> 00:01:30,118
None.

27
00:01:30,128 --> 00:01:32,148
Maybe it means something more,

28
00:01:32,148 --> 00:01:36,148
something we can’t yet understand.

29
00:01:36,148 --> 00:01:40,148
Maybe it’s some evidence,

30
00:01:40,514 --> 00:01:44,814
some artefact of a higher dimension
that we can’t consciously perceive.

31
00:01:44,814 --> 00:01:49,374
The things that we’re really
hardwired to seek:

32
00:01:49,764 --> 00:01:53,814
beauty, love, humour …

33
00:01:53,924 --> 00:01:57,984
I can’t prove to you 
that someone is beautiful.

34
00:01:57,984 --> 00:02:02,384
I can’t prove love even exists,
and statistically

35
00:02:02,384 --> 00:02:05,084
we could make a case 
that it doesn’t exist.

36
00:02:05,084 --> 00:02:08,614
And we could say, like they 
talk about the God delusion—

37
00:02:08,614 --> 00:02:11,354
we could write a book called
The Love Delusion.

38
00:02:11,354 --> 00:02:13,774
Why is everyone searching for this?
It that no one has it.

39
00:02:13,774 --> 00:02:17,044
They’re all lying to themselves.
It doesn’t really exist.

40
00:02:17,221 --> 00:02:21,051
But there’s an element 
with inside us

41
00:02:21,051 --> 00:02:24,871
that can’t accept that, 
that it doesn’t exist.

42
00:02:24,871 --> 00:02:30,942
Look, even in this world
when you deal with romantic love,

43
00:02:31,088 --> 00:02:33,121
people will meet someone
and then they’ll say,

44
00:02:33,121 --> 00:02:36,164
“I have always 
and only loved you.”

45
00:02:36,164 --> 00:02:41,247
I’m drawn across the universe
to someone I haven’t seen in a decade.

46
00:02:41,247 --> 00:02:43,927
who I know is probably dead.

47
00:02:43,927 --> 00:02:47,517
If we can feel that way
—and we want to feel that way—

48
00:02:47,517 --> 00:02:50,377
if we can feel that way
about someone in this world,

49
00:02:50,377 --> 00:02:54,478
then magnify that 
to an infinite degree,

50
00:02:55,524 --> 00:02:57,096
and you can begin
to understand

51
00:02:57,096 --> 00:03:00,066
what we’re dealing with 
in Kṛṣṇa conception;

52
00:03:00,066 --> 00:03:04,306
the compelling, irresistible,
all-attractive beauty,

53
00:03:04,306 --> 00:03:07,846
seductive charm,
sweetness of Kṛṣṇa.

54
00:03:08,196 --> 00:03:14,965
And even in the face
of heavily anti-statistical evidence

55
00:03:14,965 --> 00:03:18,268
that you won’t get it,
you’re not experiencing it,

56
00:03:18,268 --> 00:03:20,270
we’ll still search for it.

57
00:03:21,226 --> 00:03:24,546
Love is the one thing
we’re capable of perceiving

58
00:03:24,546 --> 00:03:28,356
that transcends dimensions
of time and space.

59
00:03:29,504 --> 00:03:34,214
Maybe we should trust that,
even if we can’t understand it yet.

60
00:03:35,003 --> 00:03:38,933
Try for that one thing upon getting which
you get everything.

61
00:03:39,097 --> 00:03:43,147
[Search for Reality the Beautiful]

